The paper discusses the use of naive Bayes classifiers in document classification, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of these classifiers in disease prediction, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS).
